canonical:
  title: 司宰卿崔宗峻左司郞中崔宗梓桂陽都護副使崔宗藩等讓起復不允批答
  author: 金公粹
  language: lzh
  text: 云云盡哀履戚雖孝子之執喪順變從權亦忠臣之奉國汝起從閥閱早預縉紳玉季珠昆共襲金張之貴冬溫夏凊克勤曾閔之修何辜于天遽亡所恃痛情含恤已終百日之期以義掩恩何畢三年之制毋煩陳讓斯速就官云云
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 司宰卿崔宗峻左司郞中崔宗梓桂陽都護副使崔宗藩等讓起復不允批答
  author: 金公粹
  language: lzh
  text: 云云。盡哀履戚。雖孝子之執喪。順變從權。亦忠臣之奉國。汝起從閥閱。早預縉紳。玉季珠昆。共襲金張之貴。冬溫夏凊。克勤曾閔之修。何辜于天。遽亡所恃。痛情含恤。已終百日之期。以義掩恩。何畢三年之制。毋煩陳讓。斯速就官云云。
korean:
  title: 사재경 최종준 좌사랑중 최종재 계양도호 부사 최종번 등 양 기복 불윤 비답
  author: 김공수
  language: kor
  text: 운운.애통을 다하는 것이 비록 효자가 집상(執喪)하는 도리이나, 권도(權道)를 좇아 응변(應變)함은 또한 충신이 나라를 받드는 도리이다.너희들이 높은 가문에 태어나서 일찍 높은 벼슬의 반열에 올랐다. 주옥(珠玉) 같은 형과 아우가 함께 김일제(金日磾)와 장안세(張安世)의 귀한 자리를 이어받고, 부모에게 겨울엔 따사롭게 하고 여름엔 시원하게 하여 증자(曾子)와 민자(閔子)의 효도를 닦았는데 무슨 죄를 하늘에 얻어 어버이를 잃었는가. 애통으로 거상(居喪)하면서 이미 백 일의 기한을 마쳤으니, 대의(大義)로 사사로운 은혜를 억눌러야지 어찌 삼년의 제도를 다 마치려고 하는가. 번거로이 사양하는 말을 진달하지 말고 속히 관직에 나아가라. 운운.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0330_010_0270&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Royal Edict Denying the Request for Prolonged Mourning Leave of Court Officials Choe Jong-jun, Choe Jong-jae, and Choe Jong-beon
  author: Kim Gong-sui
  language: eng
  text: '...Though to fully express one''s grief and sorrow is the way of a filial child observing mourning rites, to adapt to circumstances and follow expediency is equally the duty of a loyal minister serving the realm. You were born into an illustrious house and early entered the ranks of high office. Like precious pearls and jade, you brothers together inherit the honored positions of Kim Il-je and Zhang An-shi. In winter you warmed your parents and in summer cooled them—practicing the filial devotion of Zengzi and Minzi. What transgression against Heaven cost you your parents? Though you grieve in mourning and have already completed the hundred days, let duty temper private sorrow—why extend to the full three years of ritual? Set aside your reluctant protestations and hasten to resume your post...'
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: Kim Il-je and Zhang An-shi were celebrated Han Dynasty officials known for their loyalty and wisdom, here invoked as exemplars of noble lineage
  - key: ''
    value: The 'hundred days' refers to an intermediate mourning period, distinct from the full three-year period prescribed by traditional Chinese funeral rites
  - key: ''
    value: The edict employs the tension between filial piety and state service—a central theme in Confucian thought—to justify recalling the officials to duty
